data.enText: your sense of your own value and importance

data.chText: 他是我所见的最自负的人。
data.enText: He has the biggest ego of anyone I've ever met.

data.chText: 获得这个奖项大大增强了她的自信心。
data.enText: Winning the prize really boosted her ego .
the part of the mind that is responsible for your sense of who you are (= your identity)

tr: your consciousness of your own identity
an inflated feeling of pride in your superiority to others

value.def: Someone's ego is their sense of their own worth. For example, if someone has a large ego, they think they are very important and valuable.

example.ex: He had a massive ego, never would he admit he was wrong.
example.tran: 他自视甚高，从来不会承认自己错了。

trans: 第二自我；至交；知己；挚友
自我同一性；自我认同；自我同一性理论；自我统合；自我身份
自我表现；自我满足的行为
